THE nine pupils that were arrested for the murder of Thoriso Themane will appear in the Polokwane Magistrate's Court. On Friday, residents of Polokwane marched demanding more arrests in the murder and putting an end to gangsterism. They expressed joy when Limpopo Police Commissioner Lieutenant General Nneke Ledwaba announced that two more boys and a girl, who are also under age, were arrested. 27-year-old Themane was reportedly killed by Capricorn High School pupils last week Saturday. He was found lying along one the streets of Polokwane, he was then taken to hospital but certified dead on arrival.  